1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3306 By: Steagall
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to state government; amending Ethics
Rule 2.70 of the Rules of the Ethics Commission (74
8 O.S. 2021, Chapter 62, App.), which relates to
campaign finance; modifying threshold of
9 contributions and expenditures before a candidate
committee shall file a Statement of Organization; and
10 providing an effective date.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Ethics Rule 2.70 of the Rules of
15 the Ethics Commission (74 O.S. 2021, Chapter 62, App.), is amended
16 to read as follows:
17 Rule 2.70. Statement of Organization – Filing Time Limit
18 A Statement of Organization for a candidate committee shall be
19 filed with the Commission at any earlier time but no later than ten
20 (10) days after the candidate has accepted or expended more than One
21 Thousand Dollars ($1,000.00) any funds for his or her campaign.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
